I wish there was a way of only getting the good bits but even aggressive unfollowing and muting doesn't work...
Whenever I start actually looking at my timeline regularly something is said that makes me take a side and then I fall into the trap too.
...something that other people missed. It's a gang culture and very few people, even the good ones avoid it.
But mixed in with that is this cynicism and desperation to find fault. It's like you prove your credentials by being pissed off about...
And the bits where lovely people meet and support each other. And where we share interesting things that improve our knowledge.
I love the good bits of Twitter - the bits that are funny and relevant and respond in seconds in the most insightful and excellent ways...
ie 'Hey everyone, look at this woman that's shaming other women. What an idiot, let's tell her off aggressively and publicly.'
Twitter's doing that thing where it criticises someone for doing something by doing the exact thing it's being critical of.
